.TH "pm_qos_update_target" 9 "pm_qos_update_target" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pm_qos_update_target \- Update a list of PM QoS constraint requests.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pm_qos_update_target
.BI "(struct pm_qos_constraints *c "  ","
.BI "struct plist_node *node "  ","
.BI "enum pm_qos_req_action action "  ","
.BI "int value "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
List of PM QoS requests.
.IP "node" 12
Target list entry.
.IP "action" 12
Action to carry out (add, update or remove).
.IP "value" 12
New request value for the target list entry.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Update the given list of PM QoS constraint requests, \fIc\fP, by carrying an
\fIaction\fP involving the \fInode\fP list entry and \fIvalue\fP on it.

The recognized values of \fIaction\fP are PM_QOS_ADD_REQ (store \fIvalue\fP in \fInode\fP
and add it to the list), PM_QOS_UPDATE_REQ (remove \fInode\fP from the list, store
\fIvalue\fP in it and add it to the list again), and PM_QOS_REMOVE_REQ (remove
\fInode\fP from the list, ignore \fIvalue\fP).
.SH "RETURN"
1 if the aggregate constraint value has changed, 0  otherwise.
